==English==

===Verb===
'''to moil'''
#to toil, to work hard
#:''I do not like to moil.''
#to churn continually

===Noun===
'''moil'''
#hard work
#confusion: [[turmoil]]

===Etymology===
From Middle English 'mollen', 'to soften by wetting', from Old French 'moillier' with the same meaning, from Latin 'mollia panis', 'the soft part of bread', from 'mollis', 'soft'; from the Proto-Indo-European root 'mel-', 'soft'.

